Redescription.
Length 3.0– 
3.5 mm
. Body brown, antennae, elytra, legs, and maxillary palpi pale (
Fig. 23a
). 
Head:
Bluntly triangular, widest across eyes (
Fig. 23c
). Male antennomeres 2–3 subquadrate, 4 longer than wide, 5–10 subquadrate. Female antennomeres 2–6 longer than wide, 7–10 subquadrate. Frontal sulcus deep, reaching behind eye from end of frontal rostrum (
Fig. 23c
). Anterior frontal fovea absent (
Fig. 23c
), posterior frontal fovea elongate (
Fig. 23c
). Eye large and prominent, one-half length of temple (
Fig. 23c
). 
Thorax:
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at midpoint. Elytra rectangular in male (
Fig. 23a
), subquadrate in female. 
Abdomen:
Tergite IV with pair of transverse patches of microtrichia reaching middle in male, patches absent in female. 
Aedeagus:
Median lobe deeply divided, minor lobe longer and narrower (
Fig. 23b
). Phallobase of median lobe symmetrical and rounded (
Fig. 23b
). Parameres symmetrical, ca. 8 setae apically (
Fig. 23b
).
